Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, chop the @Bell Pepper{1}(chopped into 2cm chunks).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, fry the @British Pork Mince{240%grams}, pepper, @Sugar Snap Peas{80%grams} and @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break up the pork as it cooks, then drain the fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Stir in the @Ketjap Manis{50%grams}, @Rice Vinegar{30%milliliter}, @Soy Sauce{15%milliliter}, @Sugar{1%tsp}, @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp} (see pantry for both) and a splash of water.

Simmer, ~{1%minute}. Remove from the heat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the sweet and sticky pork.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%grams}.

Enjoy!